ğŸ“Œ Objective

To develop a machine learning model that predicts the target variable age_group:
	â€¢	Adult â†’ 0
	â€¢	Senior â†’ 1

Predictions were evaluated using the F1 Score to ensure balanced performance across both classes.

â¸»

ğŸ§¹ Data Preprocessing
	â€¢	Dropped Identifier: SEQN (not predictive)
	â€¢	Handled Missing Values:
	â€¢	Categorical columns (RIAGENDR, DIQ010, PAQ605) filled with mode
	â€¢	Numerical columns filled with mean
	â€¢	Special codes (7, 9) in PAQ605 were treated as missing
	â€¢	Label Encoding:
	â€¢	Converted age_group from string labels ("Adult", "Senior") to integers (0, 1)
	â€¢	Feature Scaling: Standardized all features using StandardScaler

â¸»

ğŸ¤– Model Training
	â€¢	Used a Random Forest Classifier with:
	â€¢	n_estimators = 200
	â€¢	random_state = 42
	â€¢	Performed an 80/20 stratified train-validation split to preserve class distribution

â¸»

ğŸ“Š Evaluation
	â€¢	The model achieved an F1 Score of 1.0 on the validation set
	â€¢	Indicates perfect classification performance on the given data (no misclassifications)

â¸»

ğŸ“ Submission
	â€¢	Final predictions on the test set were saved in a CSV file with a single column: age_group
	â€¢	Format matched the provided sample_submission.csv
